document_data.History:
Yovir served as a priest of Kelemvor and caretaker of [[Valhingen Graveyard]] for 40 years.

In the {{YearlinkName|1489}}, with rumors of [[dracolich]]es and [[ghost ship]]s wandering the [[Moonsea]] on the rise, [[Yip|a madman]] arrived in the city speaking about a ghost ship. This convinced Yovir to hire an adventuring party to investigate the matter.{{Cite adventurers league/Shadows over the Moonsea|7}}

Some time later, the growing increase of [[undead]] activities in [[Valhingen Graveyard]] inducted him to once again hire adventurers to aid the acolyte [[Cassyt]] in their investigation on the matter.{{Cite adventurers league/Dues for the Dead|7-8}}

During the coup instigated by [[Cult of the Dragon|Dragon Cultists]], Yovir was nowhere to be found.{{Cite adventurers league/Tyranny in Phlan|10}} It was later discovered that he died during the coup.{{Cite adventurers league/Reclamation of Phlan|27}}

Around the {{YearlinkName|1492}} somehow, likely with the help of the [[Dark Powers]] of [[Ravenloft]], he was raised as an undead [[vampire]]. He fought against the army that tried to reclaim the city but at was destroyed for good by some [[adventurer]]s.{{Cite adventurers league/Reclamation of Phlan|27-28}}
